article.headline: Denver 52, UC Riverside 46
article.story: DENVER -- Kyle Lewis scored 13 points as Denver won its fifth straight, beating UC Riverside 52-46 Sunday. Andrew Hooper added 11 points for Denver (6-6). The winning streak is Denver's longest since 2006. Kyle Austin led UC Riverside (7-4) with 19 points. The Highlanders missed their first five shots to start the game and didn't have a field goal until Brandon Dowdy's 3-pointer with 13:20 left in the first half. They shot 39 percent from the field in losing consecutive games for the first time this year. Denver led 32-22 at halftime. Austin's off balance jumper got the Highlanders to within 44-42 with 3:06 remaining in the game. Travis Hallam answered for Denver with a 3-pointer to make it 47-42. Two free throws by Javon Borum with 2:07 made it a 47-44 game. Rob Lewis sealed the game for Denver with a basket with 48 seconds left.
